1 Exploratory Analysis

1.1 Variability of y and X

Standardized data and box plot

library(leaps)
library(bayesreg)

setwd("~/Documents/Courses/Bayesian Econometrics - Insper/Dados")
data = read.table("gpa2.txt",header=TRUE)

n    = nrow(data)
k    = ncol(data)
data = data-matrix(apply(data,2,mean),n,k,byrow=TRUE)
for (i in 1:k){
  data[,i] = data[,i]/sqrt(var(data[,i]))
}


y = data[,1]
X = as.matrix(data[,2:k])

par(mfrow=c(1,1))
boxplot(cbind(y,X),outline=FALSE,col=c(2,rep(grey(0.8),k)))

1.2 Correlations between y and X

cors = cor(cbind(y,X))[1,2:(k)]
ind = 1:(k-1)
ord = ind[order(cors,decreasing=TRUE)]

par(mfrow=c(1,2))
plot(cors,xlab="Predictor",ylab="Correlation with Y")
abline(h=0,col=2)
plot(cors[ord],xlab="Predictor",ylab="Correlation with Y")
abline(h=0,col=2)

1.3 Singular value decomposition of X

par(mfrow=c(1,1))
svdX = svd(X)$d
plot(100*svdX/sum(svdX),xlab="Principal Component",ylab="% variabiliity")

p = length(ols$coef)

bhat = ols$coef
se   = summary(ols)$sigma*sqrt(diag(summary(ols)$cov.unscaled))
L    = bhat-2*se
U    = bhat+2*se


plot(bhat,pch=16,ylim=range(L,U))
for (i in 1:p){
  segments(i,L[i],i,U[i])
  if ((L[i]>0)|(U[i]<0)){
    text(i,max(U),i,cex=0.5)
  }
abline(h=0,lty=2)}

2.4 Regression 4: Sub-set stepwise (sequential replacement) selection

data  = data.frame(y=y,X=X)
regs  = regsubsets(y~.,data=data,method="seq",intercept=FALSE)
regs.summary = summary(regs)

par(mfrow=c(1,2))
plot(regs.summary$bic,pch=16,xlab="Number of predictors",ylab="BIC")
plot(regs,scale="bic")

bic = regs.summary$bic
ii  = 1:k
coef(regs,ii[bic==min(bic)])

3 Bayesan regularizaton

3.1 Bayesan regularizaton via ridge, Laplace & horseshoe priors

Now I use bayesreg to fit regressions with ridge, lasso and horseshoe. All priors considered pull coefficients toward zero, note that in the ridge regression this effect occurs with less intensity.

M0    = 1000
M     = 1000
skip  = 10

data1 = data.frame(y=y,X=X)
fit.r = bayesreg(y~.,data=data1,model="normal",prior="ridge",n.samples=M,burnin=M0,thin=skip)
fit.l = bayesreg(y~.,data=data1,model="normal",prior="lasso",n.samples=M,burnin=M0,thin=skip)
fit.h = bayesreg(y~.,data=data1,model="normal",prior="hs",n.samples=M,burnin=M0,thin=skip)


q.r   = t(apply(fit.r$beta,1,quantile,c(0.15,0.5,0.85)))
q.l   = t(apply(fit.l$beta,1,quantile,c(0.15,0.5,0.85)))
q.h   = t(apply(fit.h$beta,1,quantile,c(0.15,0.5,0.85)))

cond.r = ((q.r[,1]>0)|(q.r[,3]<0))
cond.l = ((q.l[,1]>0)|(q.l[,3]<0))
cond.h = ((q.h[,1]>0)|(q.h[,3]<0))

pred5.r = ind[cond.r]
pred5.l = ind[cond.l]
pred5.h = ind[cond.h]

k.r = sum(cond.r)
k.l = sum(cond.l)
k.h = sum(cond.h)

3.2 Comparing marginal posteriors distributions

par(mfrow=c(2,2),mai=c(0.5,0.5,0.5,0.5))
plot(ols$coef,xlab="Predictor",ylab="Coeffients",main="",ylim=range(L,U),pch=16,cex=0.5)
for (i in 1:p) segments(i,L[i],i,U[i])
abline(h=0,col=2)
title(paste("OLS")) 
plot(q.r[,2],xlab="Predictor",ylab="Coeffients",main="",ylim=range(q.r),pch=16,cex=0.5)
for (i in 1:11) segments(i,q.r[i,1],i,q.r[i,3])
abline(h=0,col=2)
title(paste("Ridge prior\n k=",k.r,sep=""))
plot(q.l[,2],xlab="Predictor",ylab="Coeffients",main="",ylim=range(q.l),pch=16,cex=0.5)
for (i in 1:11) segments(i,q.l[i,1],i,q.l[i,3])
abline(h=0,col=2)
title(paste("Laplace prior\n k=",k.l,sep=""))
plot(q.h[,2],xlab="Predictor",ylab="Coeffients",main="",ylim=range(q.h),pch=16,cex=0.5)
for (i in 1:11) segments(i,q.h[i,1],i,q.h[i,3])
abline(h=0,col=2)
title(paste("Horseshoe prior\n k=",k.h,sep=""))

#All three priors considered together
par(mfrow=c(1,1),mai=c(0.8,0.8,0.5,0.5))
plot(q.r[,2],xlab="Predictor",ylab="Coeffients",main="",pch=16,cex=0.5,
     col=0,axes=FALSE,ylim=range(q.r,q.l,q.h))
axis(2);box();axis(1,at=1:k)
for (i in 1:11){
  segments(i,q.r[i,1],i,q.r[i,3],col=2,lwd=2)
  segments(i+0.1,q.l[i,1],i+0.1,q.l[i,3],col=3,lwd=2)
  segments(i+0.2,q.h[i,1],i+0.2,q.h[i,3],col=4,lwd=2)
}
points(1:11,q.r[,2],pch=16,cex=0.75,col=2)
points(0.1+1:11,q.l[,2],pch=16,cex=0.75,col=3)
points(0.2+1:11,q.h[,2],pch=16,cex=0.75,col=4)
legend("topright",legend=c("RIDGE","LASSO","HORSESHOE"),col=2:4,lwd=2,bty="n")
abline(h=0,lty=2)
